                <msContents>
                  
                    <summary>Toba-Batak pustaha with various texts on magic and medicine.</summary>
                   
                    <textLang mainLang="bbc">Toba-Batak</textLang>
                    
                    <msItem n="1" xml:id="Wellcome_Batak_36801_1">
                        
                        <title>Gorak-gorahan ni manuk sitoho-toho, divination from signs in the inside of a fowl.</title>
                        
                        <note>Southern form of ta.</note>
                        
                        <note>Chain of transmission: <persName>Guru Lawan Ni Aji </persName>- <persName>Guru Laling Ni Aji</persName> - Guru
                            Bisa Mandoit (Aji) - <persName role="copyist">Datu Poduwon Ni Aji of the clan Simamora Debata Raja</persName>, the copyist - his brother-in-law Tuwan Sogar Ni Aji of
                            the clan Sitorang Na Bolon in <settlement>Situnggung</settlement>.</note>
                        
                        <note>There is a village called Situnggung in the Simalungun principality of Dolog Silou, but as Sitorang is not a Simalungun clan it is improbable that this is meant here.</note>
         
                        <note> 
                            <locusGrp>
                            <locus>a 2-62, b 2-7. There is a lacuna between a 24 and 25.</locus>
                        </locusGrp> 
                        </note>
                        
                    </msItem>
                    
                    <msItem n="2" xml:id="Wellcome_Batak_36801_2">
                        
                        <title>Pagar, panabari and pandumpang, probably all protective magic.</title>
                        
                        <note>The same handwriting as the previous text. Four magical drawings.</note>
                        
                        <note>Chain of transmission: <persName>Guru Hasiyan Ni Aji</persName>- <persName>Guru So Dapotan Ni Aji</persName>-
                        a man of the clan Simamora Debata Raja [ie <persName role="copyist">Datu Poduwon Ni Aji</persName>] - his brother-in-law of the clan
                        Sitorang Na Bolon in <settlement>Situnggung</settlement></note>
                        
                        <note> 
                            <locusGrp>
                                <locus>b 8-22.</locus>
                            </locusGrp> 
                        </note>
                        
                    </msItem>
                    
                    <msItem n="3" xml:id="Wellcome_Batak_36801_3">
                        
                        <title>Aji ginjung or aji habonaran, magic against thieves, with a figure which should be drawn on a winnowing-basket.</title>
                        
                        <note>Another hand, which uses the northern ta.</note>
                        
                        <note> 
                            <locusGrp>
                                <locus>b 23-25.</locus>
                            </locusGrp> 
                        </note>
                        
                    </msItem>
                    
                    <msItem n="4" xml:id="Wellcome_Batak_36801_4">
                        
                        <title>Pagangubalang sigundur, aggressive magic.</title>
                        
                        <note>The title only, with a chain of transmission: a teacher of the clan Padang in Pakpak - a man whose clan is indicated as anak na di Turihon in Tongging -
                            -his brother-in-law of the clan Sihotang.</note>
                        
                        <note>Cf. Voorhoeve, 1969, p. 166 f. for the expression anak na di Turihon.</note>
                        
                        <note><settlement>Tongging</settlement> is at the extreme north of <geogName>Lake Toba</geogName>.</note>
                        
                        <note> 
                            <locusGrp>
                                <locus>b 25-26.</locus>
                            </locusGrp> 
                        </note>
                        
                    </msItem>
                    
                    <msItem n="5" xml:id="Wellcome_Batak_36801_5">
                        
                        <title>Poda ni ari rojangta laho mangona ome tu juma.</title>
                        
                        <note>On choosing a propitious time for putting grains of rice into holes made with dibbles, but the subject of the text is not ari rojang (the lunar mansions,
                        cf. Voorhoeve, 1969, p. 163), but rather the signs of the zodiac and the five periods of the day.</note>
                        
                        <note>At the end there are some tables for computing lucky days.</note>
                        
                        <note> 
                            <locusGrp>
                                <locus>b 26-31</locus>
                            </locusGrp> 
                        </note>
                        
                    </msItem>
                    
                    <msItem n="6" xml:id="Wellcome_Batak_36801_6">
                        
                        <title>Poda ni si padiampa ni taun.</title>
                        
                        <note>To predict whether there will be a good harvest, in connexion with the twelve months.</note>
                        
                        <note> 
                            <locusGrp>
                                <locus>b 31-36</locus>
                            </locusGrp> 
                        </note>
                        
                    </msItem>
                    
                    <msItem n="7" xml:id="Wellcome_Batak_36801_7">
                        
                        <title>Poda ni tulbasta di begu pane.</title>
                        
                        <note>On the treatment of typhoid fever. One method is pouring water with medicinal herbs over the patient.</note>
                        
                        <note> 
                            <locusGrp>
                                <locus>b 36-41</locus>
                            </locusGrp> 
                        </note>
                        
                    </msItem>
                    
                    <msItem n="8" xml:id="Wellcome_Batak_36801_8">
                        
                        <title>Poda ni tambarta di na rojanon</title>
                        
                        <note>On a medicine against dysentery</note>
                        
                        <note> 
                            <locusGrp>
                                <locus>b 42-44.</locus>
                            </locusGrp> 
                        </note>
                        
                    </msItem>
                    
                    <msItem n="9" xml:id="Wellcome_Batak_36801_9">
                        
                        <title>On pongpang bala saribu, 'stemming a thousand warriors'. <note>In this paragraph the pupil is addressed as 'my uncle' (tulangku).</note></title>
                        
                        <note> 
                            <locusGrp>
                                <locus>b 44-45.</locus>
                            </locusGrp> 
                        </note>
                        
                    </msItem>
                    
                    <msItem n="10" xml:id="Wellcome_Batak_36801_10">
                        
                        <title>Poda ni ari rojang, on the 30 days of the month in connexion with the lunar mansions</title>
                        
                        <note>Written for <persName>Guru Gina(n?)jangan Ni Aji</persName>.</note>
                        
                        <note> 
                            <locusGrp>
                                <locus>b 45-56</locus>
                            </locusGrp> 
                        </note>
                        
                    </msItem>
                    
                    <msItem n="11" xml:id="Wellcome_Batak_36801_11">
                        
                        <title>An incantation (tabas) for protectice magic (pagar).</title>
                        
                        <note> 
                            <locusGrp>
                                <locus>b 56-59</locus>
                            </locusGrp> 
                        </note>
                        
                    </msItem>
                    
                    <msItem n="12" xml:id="Wellcome_Batak_36801_12">
                        
                        <title>Some scribbles</title>
                        
                        <note> 
                            <locusGrp>
                                <locus>b 60 and 62.</locus>
                            </locusGrp> 
                        </note>
                        
                    </msItem>
                    
                </msContents>
                
